title: Georgia - unemployment rate 1992 to 2018
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 27.
Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year '08 and '09.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 10.5 was reached at Year '10
Minimum Unemployment rate about 3.6 was reached at Year '00
